	    P. Ovidius Naso
	    The Epistles of Ovid, translated into English prose, as near the original as the different idioms of the Latin and English languages will allow;  with the Latin text and order of construction on the same page;  and critical, historical, geographical, and classical notes in English, from the very best commentators both ancient and modern;  beside a very great number of notes entirely new.

	      London
	      J. Nunn, Great-Queen-Street;  R. Priestly, 143, High-Holborn;  R. Lea, Greek-Street, Soho;  and J. Rodwell, New-Bond-Street
	      1813
